<tr>
<td width=3D"15%" valign=3D"top">
<!-- Add marginal notes below -->
<i>
Alternative Definition of Kurtosis
</i>
</td>
<td width=3D"85%">
<!-- Add main text below -->
The kurtosis for a <a href=3D"https://www.itl.nist.gov/div898/handbook/eda/=
section3/eda3661.htm">standard normal
distribution</a> is three.  For this reason, some sources
use the following definition of kurtosis (often referred to as
"excess kurtosis"):
